not listened to.

00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:36.145 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
intuitive healing

00:01:36.145 --> 00:01:39.120 align:middle line:84%
is about is bringing back
that honoring of intuition

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:42.900 align:middle line:84%
and spirituality and
along with the technology.

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:46.190 align:middle line:84%
Wedding all of these things
together to help people.

00:01:46.190 --> 00:01:48.840 align:middle line:84%
>> People come to you
as a psychiatrist.

00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:51.900 align:middle line:84%
Don't they want you to
give them the answers?

00:01:51.900 --> 00:01:53.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they want to--
they want guidance.

00:01:53.910 --> 00:01:56.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm not the type of doctor
who gives out answers,

00:01:56.220 --> 00:01:57.870 align:middle line:90%
because I don't believe in that.

00:01:57.870 --> 00:02:01.050 align:middle line:84%
But the way I do work, as an
intuitive, as a psychiatrist,

00:02:01.050 --> 00:02:04.390 align:middle line:84%
is to help people ignite
the healing in themselves.

00:02:04.390 --> 00:02:06.465 align:middle line:84%
And if I can do that
through my intuitions,

00:02:06.465 --> 00:02:09.090 align:middle line:84%
if I can do that through helping
them develop their intuitions,

00:02:09.090 --> 00:02:10.860 align:middle line:90%
this is a beautiful thing.

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:12.600 align:middle line:84%
But what happens in
the past is people

00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:15.150 align:middle line:84%
tend to disempower
themselves around doctors,

00:02:15.150 --> 00:02:17.160 align:middle line:84%
and this happens
around me a lot.

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:19.080 align:middle line:84%
Being a psychiatrist
and an intuitive,

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:22.110 align:middle line:84%
what people try and do is
disempower themselves and think

00:02:22.110 --> 00:02:23.760 align:middle line:84%
that I'll be able
to do it for them,

00:02:23.760 --> 00:02:25.560 align:middle line:84%
which is counterproductive
and it's nothing

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:26.740 align:middle line:90%
that I would ever do.

00:02:26.740 --> 00:02:28.500 align:middle line:84%
My job is to
empower other people

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:29.970 align:middle line:90%
to develop their intuitions.

00:02:29.970 --> 00:02:31.470 align:middle line:84%
>> But don't they
fight you on that?

00:02:31.470 --> 00:02:31.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yeah.

00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:32.700 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:02:32.700 --> 00:02:33.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Don't they say, well,
you're an intuitive.

00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:35.670 align:middle line:84%
Tell me what's going to
happen with my boyfriend.

00:02:35.670 --> 00:02:36.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, they do.

00:02:36.270 --> 00:02:37.740 align:middle line:84%
They always try
to-- even patients

00:02:37.740 --> 00:02:40.230 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with a long
time they try and catch me

00:02:40.230 --> 00:02:41.735 align:middle line:90%
with that, but I never do.

00:02:41.735 --> 00:02:43.860 align:middle line:84%
Always, when I do intuitive
readings with patients,

00:02:43.860 --> 00:02:45.660 align:middle line:84%
I ask them to do
intuitive readings too

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:47.520 align:middle line:84%
and then we correlate
ours together.

00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:49.440 align:middle line:84%
It's all about
empowering people,

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:51.660 align:middle line:84%
because we all have this
capacity to tune in.

00:02:51.660 --> 00:02:54.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm certainly not the
only one who can do that.

00:02:54.510 --> 00:02:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And everyone needs to
be able to do that.

00:02:57.060 --> 00:02:59.430 align:middle line:84%
And the beautiful thing working
with patients in therapy

00:02:59.430 --> 00:03:01.198 align:middle line:84%
is once they're
able to get in touch

00:03:01.198 --> 00:03:03.240 align:middle line:84%
with their intuitive voice,
then, a lot of times,

00:03:03.240 --> 00:03:04.950 align:middle line:84%
they can leave
therapy, and no matter

00:03:04.950 --> 00:03:06.450 align:middle line:84%
what they go through
in their lives,

00:03:06.450 --> 00:03:08.283 align:middle line:84%
all of the ups and downs
they have something

00:03:08.283 --> 00:03:10.590 align:middle line:84%
to turn to inside
to listen to that

00:03:10.590 --> 00:03:12.450 align:middle line:84%
will tell them the
truth about things.

00:03:12.450 --> 00:03:14.370 align:middle line:84%
And this is the
beginning of my therapy

00:03:14.370 --> 00:03:16.110 align:middle line:84%
with every patient
is teaching them

00:03:16.110 --> 00:03:18.210 align:middle line:84%
to get in touch with
this intuitive voice

00:03:18.210 --> 00:03:21.220 align:middle line:84%
and dealing with all the
resistances to doing so.

00:03:21.220 --> 00:03:25.570 align:middle line:84%
>> You say there are five ways
to start getting in touch with

00:03:25.570 --> 00:03:26.370 align:middle line:90%
your--

00:03:26.370 --> 00:03:26.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:03:26.610 --> 00:03:27.480 align:middle line:90%
>> --intuitive voice.

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:28.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:03:28.280 --> 00:03:30.480 align:middle line:84%
I go through five steps
in intuitive healing,

00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:33.330 align:middle line:84%
and these really are the
steps I live in my own life

00:03:33.330 --> 00:03:36.120 align:middle line:84%
and teach to my patients
about developing intuition.

00:03:36.120 --> 00:03:39.600 align:middle line:84%
And they are, one, noticing
your beliefs about healing, two,

00:03:39.600 --> 00:03:41.910 align:middle line:84%
being in your body,
three, learning

00:03:41.910 --> 00:03:44.520 align:middle line:84%
to sense your subtle
energies, four,

00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:48.390 align:middle line:84%
asking for inner guidance,
and five, listening to dreams.

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:49.920 align:middle line:84%
And in the book,
in each chapter,

00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:52.440 align:middle line:84%
I go through the five steps
in every single chapter

00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:54.870 align:middle line:84%
as a strategy for
dealing with any problem

00:03:54.870 --> 00:03:56.650 align:middle line:90%
that you'll ever deal with.

00:03:56.650 --> 00:03:58.950 align:middle line:84%
And this is a way of
seeing beyond surfaces

00:03:58.950 --> 00:04:00.920 align:middle line:84%
and getting to a
sense of truth within.

00:04:00.920 --> 00:04:01.720 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:04:01.720 --> 00:04:04.110 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about depression.

00:04:04.110 --> 00:04:05.080 align:middle line:90%
Notice your belief.

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:10.140 align:middle line:84%
Sorry, my belief is that my
mother was a manic depressive,

00:04:10.140 --> 00:04:12.600 align:middle line:84%
my grandmother was
a manic depressive.

00:04:12.600 --> 00:04:16.320 align:middle line:84%
I had two cousins who
have committed suicide.

00:04:16.320 --> 00:04:20.490 align:middle line:90%
So naturally, I am a depressive.

00:04:20.490 --> 00:04:21.670 align:middle line:90%
Give me some pills.

00:04:21.670 --> 00:04:22.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Mhm.

00:04:22.470 --> 00:04:23.490 align:middle line:90%
Mhm.

00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:23.700 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:04:23.700 --> 00:04:25.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is one
of the premises

00:04:25.050 --> 00:04:26.550 align:middle line:84%
that I really
challenge in the book.

00:04:26.550 --> 00:04:29.670 align:middle line:84%
And that we have to be very
careful to use intuition

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:31.857 align:middle line:84%
to not take on the
diseases of our lineage,

00:04:31.857 --> 00:04:33.690 align:middle line:84%
because I think we make
a mistake with that.

00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:35.340 align:middle line:84%
And there's a tendency
to over identify

00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:37.830 align:middle line:84%
with parents or our
own lineage and say,

00:04:37.830 --> 00:04:39.510 align:middle line:90%
we're going to get this too.

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:42.000 align:middle line:84%
And I came upon this
in a very personal way

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:43.860 align:middle line:84%
after my mother died
of lymphoma and then

00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:45.555 align:middle line:84%
my father died of
Parkinson's disease.

00:04:45.555 --> 00:04:47.930 align:middle line:84%
I was going through this little
box that they left for me

00:04:47.930 --> 00:04:50.250 align:middle line:84%
and had all the most
precious things in my life.

00:04:50.250 --> 00:04:53.400 align:middle line:84%
It had my first baby hair,
it had all of my report cards

00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:55.590 align:middle line:84%
from when I was a little
girl, and they kept all

00:04:55.590 --> 00:04:57.180 align:middle line:90%
these little milestones for me.

00:04:57.180 --> 00:05:02.220 align:middle line:84%
But also in this box was a
piece of paper dated 1976, which

00:05:02.220 --> 00:05:05.490 align:middle line:84%
was the initial diagnosis
of my mother's lymphoma,

00:05:05.490 --> 00:05:08.190 align:middle line:84%
and she put it in the box
with all of my milestones.

00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:10.200 align:middle line:84%
And my first reaction
was, oh my god,

00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:11.850 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to get lymphoma too.

00:05:11.850 --> 00:05:13.717 align:middle line:84%
And at that moment,
I said, no, stop.

00:05:13.717 --> 00:05:14.550 align:middle line:90%
You have to tune in.

00:05:14.550 --> 00:05:17.130 align:middle line:84%
You have to use your intuition
to see if this is true.

00:05:17.130 --> 00:05:20.390 align:middle line:84%
And I tuned in and I got
definitely it wasn't true,

00:05:20.390 --> 00:05:22.410 align:middle line:84%
but that no matter how
much I love my mother,

00:05:22.410 --> 00:05:25.470 align:middle line:84%
I had to disengage from
her patterns of physical

00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:28.380 align:middle line:84%
and emotional illness
that I didn't necessarily

00:05:28.380 --> 00:05:29.730 align:middle line:90%
have to take on.

00:05:29.730 --> 00:05:31.530 align:middle line:90%
And I think that's important.

00:05:31.530 --> 00:05:32.550 align:middle line:90%
Genetics are important.

00:05:32.550 --> 00:05:34.470 align:middle line:84%
I think it behooves
us to honor them,

00:05:34.470 --> 00:05:36.060 align:middle line:90%
but they're not everything.

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:38.440 align:middle line:84%
And the parents-- the
patterns of our parents,

00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:41.860 align:middle line:84%
we don't have to take on if
we do our own healing work.

00:05:41.860 --> 00:05:43.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you give any of
your patients medication?

00:05:43.830 --> 00:05:44.630 align:middle line:90%
>> I do.

00:05:44.630 --> 00:05:46.255 align:middle line:84%
Actually, there's a
section in the book

00:05:46.255 --> 00:05:48.150 align:middle line:84%
on the intuitive
use of medications,

00:05:48.150 --> 00:05:50.640 align:middle line:90%
antidepressants anti-anxieties.

00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:53.160 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, particularly
with depression,

00:05:53.160 --> 00:05:55.860 align:middle line:84%
certain people have
a lack of serotonin.

00:05:55.860 --> 00:05:57.810 align:middle line:84%
And with that lack
of serotonin, it's

00:05:57.810 --> 00:06:00.450 align:middle line:84%
like going uphill
to find your center.

00:06:00.450 --> 00:06:03.780 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes the best solution
is to take antidepressants

00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:06.150 align:middle line:84%
for a short period of
time, or for some people

00:06:06.150 --> 00:06:07.890 align:middle line:84%
need to be on at a
lifetime, you know,

00:06:07.890 --> 00:06:09.503 align:middle line:90%
and God bless if that's so.

00:06:09.503 --> 00:06:10.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, I have no
judgment about that

00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:12.960 align:middle line:84%
at all, but what I'm
very strong about

00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:15.193 align:middle line:84%
is if someone's on
medication that I also

00:06:15.193 --> 00:06:16.860 align:middle line:84%
do intuitive work
within them and I also

00:06:16.860 --> 00:06:19.660 align:middle line:84%
do spiritual work with them and
they listen to their bodies,

00:06:19.660 --> 00:06:22.570 align:middle line:84%
listen to their body
energies with the medication

00:06:22.570 --> 00:06:23.370 align:middle line:90%
in their system.

00:06:23.370 --> 00:06:26.670 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that medication,
everything has a spirit to it.

00:06:26.670 --> 00:06:28.950 align:middle line:84%
And if we could intuitively
connect with the spirit--

00:06:28.950 --> 00:06:30.120 align:middle line:90%
even let's say a Prozac.

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:31.680 align:middle line:90%
Prozac has a spirit.

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:33.450 align:middle line:84%
And if we can connect
with it, then we

00:06:33.450 --> 00:06:35.860 align:middle line:84%
can work with this
substance in our system

00:06:35.860 --> 00:06:38.318 align:middle line:84%
so it's not just an
alien substance roaming

00:06:38.318 --> 00:06:40.110 align:middle line:84%
around doing as it
will, but it's something

00:06:40.110 --> 00:06:42.160 align:middle line:84%
that we can intuitively
connect with.

00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:44.340 align:middle line:84%
And so if one of my
patients is on medication,

00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:46.650 align:middle line:84%
I work with them to tune
into their intuition

00:06:46.650 --> 00:06:48.840 align:middle line:90%
and open up spiritually.

00:06:48.840 --> 00:06:51.272 align:middle line:84%
The psychopharmacologist who
just writes a prescription

00:06:51.272 --> 00:06:52.980 align:middle line:84%
and sends someone home
with a medication,

00:06:52.980 --> 00:06:54.740 align:middle line:90%
I'm very much against.

00:06:54.740 --> 00:06:56.365 align:middle line:84%
>> But that seems to
be a tendency now.

00:06:56.365 --> 00:06:57.165 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh that's--

00:06:57.165 --> 00:06:58.410 align:middle line:90%
>> The 15-minute appointment.

00:06:58.410 --> 00:06:59.243 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, that's right.

00:06:59.243 --> 00:07:00.990 align:middle line:84%
That's a whole
trend in psychiatry

00:07:00.990 --> 00:07:02.550 align:middle line:84%
now is the easy
fix with the pill.

00:07:02.550 --> 00:07:04.950 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not against
correcting biochemistry,

00:07:04.950 --> 00:07:08.100 align:middle line:84%
because I know how devastating
depression can feel.

00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:10.470 align:middle line:84%
When someone is very depressed,
they could have the most

00:07:10.470 --> 00:07:13.053 align:middle line:84%
beautiful rose in front of them
and they cannot see the beauty

00:07:13.053 --> 00:07:14.027 align:middle line:90%
of it, they can't.

00:07:14.027 --> 00:07:16.110 align:middle line:84%
And they can't connect
with their sense of spirit,

00:07:16.110 --> 00:07:20.310 align:middle line:84%
they can't meditate, because the
biochemistry is stopping them.

00:07:20.310 --> 00:07:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And so sometimes medication
is the most compassionate way

00:07:23.300 --> 00:07:24.100 align:middle line:90%
to go.

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:26.700 align:middle line:84%
But each person has to
tune in to whether or not

00:07:26.700 --> 00:07:29.010 align:middle line:84%
that's the way for them
and also to tune in

00:07:29.010 --> 00:07:30.390 align:middle line:90%
to know when to go off of it.

00:07:30.390 --> 00:07:32.520 align:middle line:84%
My patients will come
to me and say, I really

00:07:32.520 --> 00:07:35.130 align:middle line:84%
think now's the time to
start decreasing the dosage.

00:07:35.130 --> 00:07:38.590 align:middle line:84%
And I honor their response
and I listen to my patients,

00:07:38.590 --> 00:07:40.710 align:middle line:84%
and that's part of how
I work as an intuitive

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:43.260 align:middle line:84%
and teach my patients
to intuitively connect

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:45.120 align:middle line:84%
with whatever is going
on in their bodies,

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:46.470 align:middle line:84%
including putting
a substance in it.

00:07:46.470 --> 00:07:46.570 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:07:46.570 --> 00:07:48.490 align:middle line:84%
So the next one said,
be in your body.

00:07:48.490 --> 00:07:49.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:49.290 --> 00:07:50.957 align:middle line:84%
>> What does that
mean, be in your body?

00:07:50.957 --> 00:07:53.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, I feel passionately
about this step.

00:07:53.010 --> 00:07:54.690 align:middle line:84%
Because being in
the body is a way

00:07:54.690 --> 00:07:57.180 align:middle line:84%
of listening to the intuitive
signals in the body.

00:07:57.180 --> 00:07:59.310 align:middle line:84%
It means being
centrally connected

00:07:59.310 --> 00:08:01.620 align:middle line:84%
to the feelings in
the body, but also, it

00:08:01.620 --> 00:08:04.770 align:middle line:84%
means learning about our
internal workings of our body.

00:08:04.770 --> 00:08:06.810 align:middle line:84%
And I suggest to everyone
to go out and buy

00:08:06.810 --> 00:08:10.740 align:middle line:84%
"Gray's Anatomy" coloring book
to learn where our organs are.

00:08:10.740 --> 00:08:12.930 align:middle line:84%
It is just amazing
to me how most people

00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:15.090 align:middle line:84%
go through a lifetime
and never know

00:08:15.090 --> 00:08:16.290 align:middle line:90%
what they look like inside.

00:08:16.290 --> 00:08:19.140 align:middle line:84%
Not only that, we're brought
up with a tremendous revulsion

00:08:19.140 --> 00:08:20.790 align:middle line:84%
of the human body
and secretions,

00:08:20.790 --> 00:08:22.860 align:middle line:84%
and this stops our
